        <abstract>
            <p>CD writes for Emma, who is ill.</p> 
<p>Delighted with FPC’s "most just" article [in <hi rend="italic">Echo</hi>?]. Sends £1 subscription.</p>  
<p>Thanks for telling CD about the <hi rend="italic">Fraser’s Magazine</hi> article [F. W. Farrar, "Hereditary genius (by F. Galton)", n.s. 2 (1870): 251–65].</p> 
            <p>CD wrote as Justice of Peace for Kent to the Home Secretary about Holder’s case.</p> 
<p><hi rend="italic">Tropaeolum</hi> transmits every shade of colour if self-fertilised for six or seven generations.</p> 
        </abstract>
